message: Cantonese is not the Standard Chinese

Cantonese is not a standardised form because it is not an official language of the U.N. or China. It is only spoken as a local dialect in the Guangdong area. Mandarin or Standard Chinese is the official language of both PRC and ROC. Also, in schools (A...
